Thai Flood May Cut 2011 Growth to 3%-3.5%, University Forecasts

-- B y   S u t t i n e e   Y u v e j w a t t a n a
-- 
2011-10-13T04:24:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/thai-flood-may-cut-2011-growth-to-3-3-5-university-forecasts.html
The University of the Thai Chamber
of Commerce cut its estimate for  Thailand ’s economic growth
because of the rising cost of damage caused by flooding.  Thailand’s economy may expand by 3 percent to 3.5 percent
this year, the university said today. Damage caused by the
disaster may rise to 156.7 billion baht, the university said.  The university earlier estimated damage at 104 billion
baht.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Suttinee Yuvejwattana in Bangkok at 
 suttinee1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
